  <S>The whole moon and the entire sky_x000A_Are reflected in one dewdrop on the grass.</S>
  <S>This is how your mind is._x000A_Its light penetrates everywhere_x000A_And engulfs everything,_x000A_So why does it not know itself?</S>
  <S>Who is hearing?_x000A_Your physical being doesn't hear,_x000A_Nor does the void._x000A_Then what does?</S>
  <S>Mountains are merely mountains.</S>
  <S>Hell is not punishment; it is training.</S>
  <S>Do not mistake any state for_x000A_Self-realisation, but continueTo ask yourself even more intensely,_x000A_What is it that hears?</S>
  <S>The most important thing is to find out what is the most important thing.</S>
  <S>If you want to be free,_x000A_Get to know your real self.</S>
  <S>Knowledge and ignorance are interdependent;_x000A_Delusion and enlightenment condition each other.</S>
  <S>Even if you speak of the wonder of it all,_x000A_How do you deal with each thing changing?</S>
