  <S>When you smash the citadel of doubt,_x000A_Then the Buddha is simply yourself.</S>
  <S>I see mountains once again as mountains,_x000A_And waters once again as waters.</S>
  <S>When the many are reduced to one,_x000A_To what is the one reduced?</S>
  <S>Everything the same,_x000A_Everything distinct.</S>
  <S>Make the mountains dance.</S>
  <S>No one is injured but by himself.</S>
  <S>Each branch of coral holds up the moon.</S>
